<subSubSection id="C3306530FFA0DF30B3B17DB5FB62F88B" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B9536BBFFA0DF30B3B17DB5FB62F88B" blockId="12.[191,1440,1761,1888]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B95EEAA9FFA0DF30B3B17DB5FEEEF910" bold="true" box="[192,316,1761,1787]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D38FFA0DF30B2337DB5FDBEF910" authorityName="Brown and Razowski" authorityYear="2022" box="[322,620,1761,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Eucosmocydia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deinbolliana">
<emphasis id="B95EEAA9FFA0DF30B2337DB5FDBEF910" box="[322,620,1761,1787]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Eucosmocydia deinbolliana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D38FFA0DF30B0897DB6FB46F910" authorityName="Brown and Razowski" authorityYear="2022" box="[1016,1172,1761,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Eucosmocydia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pancoviana">
<emphasis id="B95EEAA9FFA0DF30B0897DB6FBDAF910" box="[1016,1032,1762,1787]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B95EEAA9FFA0DF30B7647DB6FB46F910" box="[1045,1172,1762,1787]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">pancoviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with both the forewing and the hindwing mostly dark brown. It can be distinguished from the latter by the orange rather than leaden gray scales in the distal half of the forewing, and by the more expanded patch of pale scales on the undersurface of the hindwing. Males are easily distinguished by the shape of the sclerite of segment 7 (
<figureCitation id="13112A3EFFA0DF30B7227C12FB76F88B" box="[1107,1188,1862,1888]" captionStart="Figures 28–35" captionStartId="17.[192,279,1799,1825]" captionTargetBox="[284,1348,216,1770]" captionTargetId="figure-82@17.[284,1351,216,1770]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figures 28–35. Abdominal segment 7 of males of Eucosmocydia. 28) E. pappeana, USNM slide 143,426. 29) E. ugandensis, NHMO slide 3762. 30) E. deinbolliana, USNM slide 153,700. 31) E. lecaniodiscana, USNM slide 153,704. 32) E. nigeriana, USNM slide 153,740. 33) E. pancoviana, USNM slide 153,695. 34) E. chlorobathra, USNM slide 153,691. 35) E. kirimiriana, USNM slide 143,441." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533444" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533444/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
